name: Tamaraw Holo Rare
description:
Tamaraw project aims to raise funds for the conservation of Tamaraw in Mindoro Philippines. Tamaraw “Dwarf Buffalo”, is a critically endangered animal and one of the endemic species in the Philippines.

Many conservation groups are working hard to ensure the long-term survival of the tamaraw by conducting scientific research, preserving and restoring natural habitat, and expanding tamaraw population.
